            "answer_text": "You should have 3 things for that You require 2 Ram Slots to add another 8GB to your existing 2GB, if you have a very old system than you might only have 1 slot in which case you will have to swap out your existing 2GBs and add 8GBsYou require 64-Bit OS because 32-Bit dosent support more than 4GB ram hence even if you add 8GB and make it 2+8=10GB Ram, and your System is 32-Bit then it will only recognize 4 out of it so only 64-Bit has capacity to Use your whole 10GBs of RamCheck first before buying the Ram so as to match the required type and frequency of RAM (You cannot add a DDR4 ram to DDR3 type slot but you can add a DDR2 to DDR3 type slot)",
